<subSubSection id="C33827A8FF80FFC8B4F9FE84FE481248" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9D7423FF80FFC8B4F9FE84FE481248" blockId="1.[136,1452,280,522]" pageId="1" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF80FFC8B4F9FE84FE951138" bold="true" box="[189,304,352,378]" pageId="1" pageNumber="91">Diagnosis</emphasis>
:—This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF80FFC8B62BFE85FB101138" authority="(Chen 1987: 69) Tanaka (2003: 332)" authorityName="Tanaka" authorityPageNumber="332" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="Chen" baseAuthorityPageNumber="69" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[623,1205,352,379]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verruculosa">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF80FFC8B62BFE85FCB11138" box="[623,788,352,378]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="91">R. verruculosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB309D2FF80FFC8B766FE84FC6F1139" author="Chen, J. H." box="[802,970,352,379]" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" pagination="69 - 70" refId="ref2234" refString="Chen, J. H. (1987) A new species of Tupistra (Liliaceae) from Guizhou. Acta Phytotaxonomica Sinica 25 (1): 69 - 70." type="journal article" year="1987">Chen 1987: 69</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB309D2FF80FFC8B79CFE84FB101138" author="Tanaka, N." box="[984,1205,352,378]" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" pagination="329 - 333" refId="ref2636" refString="Tanaka, N. (2003) New combinations in Rohdea (Convallariaceae). Novon 13: 329 - 333. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3393269" type="journal article" year="2003">Tanaka (2003: 332)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs mainly by bracts 3 per flower, with several sterile bracts apically; outer bract ca. 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF80FFC8B7D2FE60FC4711DD" box="[918,994,388,415]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" unit="cm" value="4.5">4.5 cm</quantity>
long, ca. 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF80FFC8B00BFE60FB2A11DD" box="[1103,1167,388,415]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
broad; perianth globular; lobes shorter ca. 2.0 mm long, margin lacerated, apical subacut; the top of annular appendage margin lacerated, 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF80FFC8B12FFE4CFA091181" box="[1387,1452,424,451]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
above the the top of perianth tube; stigma bend, without lobed; style conspicuous; ovary globose or subglobose, askew; berry and seed ellipsoid, askew.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
