<paragraph id="8B9D7423FF83FFCBB4CCFB65FA3814F9" blockId="2.[136,1452,1153,1211]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF83FFCBB4CCFB65FF5B14D4" bold="true" box="[136,254,1153,1175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF83FFCBB541FB65FE6014D4" authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Q. W. LIN" authorityYear="2022" box="[261,453,1153,1174]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="medogensis">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF83FFCBB541FB65FE6014D4" box="[261,453,1153,1174]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Rohdea medogensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Originally collected by Feng Hui Zhe and Gong Zheng in Tibet, Medog County, Beibeng, ca.1000 m. Cultivated in Zaozhuang University. A. Habit. B. Inflorescence and fruits. C. Fruits. D. Seeds. E &amp; F. Pistils, E. Top view; F. Side view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C33827A8FF83FFCBB4F9FB0EFB9A1762" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9D7423FF83FFCBB4F9FB0EFB9A1762" blockId="2.[136,1452,1258,2076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF83FFCBB4F9FB0EFEE21546" bold="true" box="[189,327,1258,1284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Description</emphasis>
:—Chamaephytic herb. Rhizome cylindrical, usually erect, to 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB7BCFB0EFBE61546" box="[1016,1091,1258,1285]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="cm" value="2.5">2.5 cm</quantity>
in diameter, 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB097FB0EFA801546" box="[1235,1317,1258,1285]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="cm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 cm</quantity>
long. Roots fibrous, to 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB4BAFAEAFE9B156A" box="[254,318,1294,1320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
in diameter. Stem (aerial part) short, up to 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB74BFAEAFCE1156A" box="[783,836,1294,1321]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="cm" value="5.0">5 cm</quantity>
long. Leaves equitant, narrowly oblanceolate, narrowly elliptic or lorate, acute to acuminate at apex, tapering gradually to petiole-like base, subcoriaceous, 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB0BDFAD6FACF150E" box="[1273,1386,1330,1357]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="cm" value="37.5" valueMax="55.0" valueMin="20.0">20–55 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB4CCFAB2FF791532" box="[136,220,1366,1392]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="cm" value="5.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="3.0">3–8 cm</quantity>
wide. Peduncle ca. 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB586FAB2FE5F1532" box="[450,506,1366,1392]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="cm" value="3.0">3 cm</quantity>
long. Spike cylindrical or ellipsoid, with ca. 6 flowers, ca. 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB0E4FAB2FB7D1532" box="[1184,1240,1366,1393]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="cm" value="5.0">5 cm</quantity>
long, with several sterile bracts apically. Bracts 3 per flower, often minutely denticulate at margin, herbaceous or membranous; outer bract 1, borne slightly below flower, exceeding flower, lanceolate or narrowly deltoid, acute, 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB0EDFA7AFB5815FA" box="[1193,1277,1438,1465]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="cm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB102FA7AFA0915FA" box="[1350,1452,1438,1464]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2– 3 mm</quantity>
broad; inner bract (bracteole) 2, subulate, to 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB63DFA26FD1F159E" box="[633,698,1474,1500]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB744FA26FCD7159E" box="[768,882,1474,1501]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
broad, with several sterile bracts apically. Perianth globular, green, turning yellow or orange with age, 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB6FFFA02FC801642" box="[699,805,1510,1536]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8–10 mm</quantity>
across; lobes deltoid-ovate, lacerated, often abaxially with verruculose long margins, 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB5F1F9EEFDB61666" box="[437,531,1546,1572]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB618F9EEFD1F1666" box="[604,698,1546,1572]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
wide; tube cupulate, 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB7EAF9EEFB841666" box="[942,1057,1546,1573]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="3.25" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5–4 mm</quantity>
long, at orifice of tube developing annulus (or annular ledge) appendages, 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB600F9CAFD10160A" box="[580,693,1582,1609]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1–1.5 mm</quantity>
broad. The annulus appendages and tube formed a capsule chamber that encloses the pistil, and there is only a small hole in the center, diam. 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB780F9B6FBA4162E" box="[964,1025,1618,1644]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="1.0">1mm</quantity>
, lacerated. The stamens are above the annulus appendages. Anther oblong or ovate, 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB6C8F992FCB616D2" box="[652,787,1654,1681]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="1.15" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1.5 mm</quantity>
long, connectives sometimes corniculate dorsally, cornicle up to 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB483F97EFEB916F6" box="[199,284,1690,1717]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
long; filaments incurved, 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB67BF97EFD3916F6" box="[575,668,1690,1716]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 mm</quantity>
long, inserted in upper part of perianth tube, decurrent parts lamellate, dilated below, united with adjacent ones in lower part of tube. Pistil ca. 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB7EEF95AFC4E169A" box="[938,1003,1726,1753]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
long; stigma bend and not lobbed; style columnar, conspicuous, 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB5DCF906FDBA16BE" box="[408,543,1762,1789]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="3.5">3.5–5.5 mm</quantity>
long; ovary globose or subglobose, askew, 2.5–3.0 mm in diam. Berry ellipsoid, askew, ca. 
<quantity id="4CDAD9C6FF83FFCBB545F8E2FEE81762" box="[257,333,1798,1825]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" unit="cm" value="2.5">2.5 cm</quantity>
long, scarlet at maturity. Seed ellipsoid, askew, ca. 1.0 cm in diam.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33827A8FF83FFCBB4F9F8CEFEB7172A" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9D7423FF83FFCBB4F9F8CEFEB7172A" blockId="2.[136,1452,1258,2076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF83FFCBB4F9F8CEFE9B1706" bold="true" box="[189,318,1834,1860]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Etymology</emphasis>
:—The new species from Motuo (=Medog) country, we therefore give the epithet 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF83FFCBB112F8CEFEAE172A" authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Q. W. LIN" authorityYear="2022" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="medogensis">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF83FFCBB112F8CEFEAE172A" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Rohdea medogensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33827A8FF83FFCAB4F9F896FBB5119A" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="93" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B9D7423FF83FFCBB4F9F896FB6E17CE" blockId="2.[136,1452,1258,2076]" box="[189,1227,1906,1932]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF83FFCBB4F9F896FEEA17CE" bold="true" box="[189,335,1906,1932]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Distribution</emphasis>
:—This new species is currently known only from Motuo, Linzhi, 
<collectingRegion id="49E6BAC1FF83FFCBB07CF896FBD017CE" box="[1080,1141,1906,1932]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Tibet</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33534B3FF83FFCBB0C4F896FB6217CE" box="[1152,1223,1906,1932]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D7423FF83FFCAB4F9F872FBB5119A" blockId="2.[136,1452,1258,2076]" lastBlockId="3.[136,1452,158,473]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="93" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF83FFCBB4F9F872FE4717F2" bold="true" box="[189,482,1942,1968]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Taxonomic relationships</emphasis>
:—The comparisons with the known species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF83FFCBB7BCF872FBEB17F2" authorityName="Roth" authorityYear="1821" box="[1016,1102,1942,1968]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF83FFCBB7BCF872FBEB17F2" box="[1016,1102,1942,1968]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Rohdea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
indicates that 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF83FFCBB0B4F873FA3717F2" authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Q. W. LIN" authorityYear="2022" box="[1264,1426,1942,1968]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="medogensis">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF83FFCBB0B4F873FA3717F2" box="[1264,1426,1942,1968]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">R. medogensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF83FFCBB4BDF85FFE3B1796" authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="Chen" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[249,414,1978,2004]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verruculosa">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF83FFCBB4BDF85FFE3B1796" box="[249,414,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">R. verruculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF83FFCBB5EFF85FFD8B1796" box="[427,558,1978,2004]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="annulata">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF83FFCBB5EFF85FFD8B1796" box="[427,558,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">R. annulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Li &amp; Huang in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB309D2FF83FFCBB6ACF85EFC7C1797" author="Huang, J. L. &amp; Li, H." box="[744,985,1978,2005]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" pagination="49 - 61" refId="ref2353" refString="Huang, J. L. &amp; Li, H. (1990) Study on the taxonomic system of the genus Tupistra. Acta Botanica Yunnanica 12 (S 3): 49 - 61." type="journal article" year="1990">Huang &amp; Li 1990: 51</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB309D2FF83FFCBB7A3F85EFAFB1797" author="Yamashita, J. &amp; Tamura, M. N." box="[999,1374,1978,2005]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" pagination="363 - 370" refId="ref2786" refString="Yamashita, J. &amp; Tamura, M. N. (2004) Phylogenetic analyses and chromosome evolution in Convallarieae (Ruscaceae sensu lato), with some taxonomic treatments. Journal of Plant Research 117: 363 - 370. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10265 - 004 - 0169 - z" type="journal article" year="2004">Yamashita &amp; Tamura (2004: 369)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF83FFCBB1D7F85FFD9D17BA" authority="Tanaka, Hannon &amp; Averyanov" authorityName="Tanaka, Hannon &amp; Averyanov" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="harderi">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF83FFCBB1D7F85FFF7E17BA" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">R. harderi</emphasis>
Tanaka, Hannon &amp; Averyanov
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB309D2FF83FFCBB618F83AFCFB17BA" author="Tanaka, N. &amp; Hannon, D. P. &amp; Harder, D. K. &amp; Averyanov, L. V. &amp; Lahmeyer, S. C." box="[604,862,2014,2040]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" pagination="31 - 37" refId="ref2668" refString="Tanaka, N., Hannon, D. P., Harder, D. K., Averyanov, L. V. &amp; Lahmeyer, S. C. (2018) Rohdea harderi (Asparagaceae), a new species from northern Vietnam. Kew Bulletin 73 (3): 31 - 37. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12225 - 018 - 9756 - 3" type="journal article" year="2018">
Tanaka 
<emphasis id="B956A831FF83FFCBB6F1F83BFD4B17BA" box="[693,750,2014,2040]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">et al.</emphasis>
(2018: 2)
</bibRefCitation>
by stamens enclosed annulus appendage or stamens situated outer annulus appendage while other species as 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF83FFCBB74AF7E7FB54185E" authority="Handel-Mazzetti (1920: 272)" authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityPageNumber="272" authorityYear="1920" box="[782,1265,2050,2076]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uropetala">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF83FFCBB74AF7E7FC3E185E" box="[782,923,2050,2076]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">R. uropetala</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB309D2FF83FFCBB7E0F7E6FB54185E" author="Handel-Mazzetti, H. R. E." box="[932,1265,2050,2076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" pagination="253 - 256" refId="ref2266" refString="Handel-Mazzetti, H. R. E. (1920) Tupistra fimbriata. Anzeiger der Akademie der Wissenschaften in Wien, vol 59. Mathematischenaturwissenchaftliche Klasse, Wien. pp. 253 - 256." type="book chapter" year="1920">Handel-Mazzetti (1920: 272)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF83FFCBB0BAF7E7FA0E185E" box="[1278,1451,2050,2076]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lichuanensis">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF83FFCBB0BAF7E7FA0E185E" box="[1278,1451,2050,2076]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">R. lichuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Yang, Wu &amp; Peng in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB309D2FF82FFCAB5CAFF7BFD2110FA" author="Wang, F. &amp; Yang, Y. &amp; Wu, J. &amp; Peng, D." box="[398,644,158,185]" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" pagination="40 - 42" refId="ref2744" refString="Wang, F., Yang, Y., Wu, J. &amp; Peng, D. (1991) A new species of Tupistra Ker-gawl from Hubei. Journal of Wuhan Botanical Research 9: 40 - 42." type="journal article" year="1991">
Wang 
<emphasis id="B956A831FF82FFCAB59CFF7BFDA810FA" box="[472,525,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">et al</emphasis>
. 1991: 40
</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB309D2FF82FFCAB6D1FF7AFBBC10FB" author="Yamashita, J. &amp; Tamura, M. N." box="[661,1049,158,185]" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" pagination="363 - 370" refId="ref2786" refString="Yamashita, J. &amp; Tamura, M. N. (2004) Phylogenetic analyses and chromosome evolution in Convallarieae (Ruscaceae sensu lato), with some taxonomic treatments. Journal of Plant Research 117: 363 - 370. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10265 - 004 - 0169 - z" type="journal article" year="2004">Yamashita &amp; Tamura (2004: 369)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF82FFCAB011FF7BFEC1109E" authority="(Zhu 1982: 271) Tanaka (2003: 332)" authorityName="Tanaka" authorityPageNumber="332" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="Zhu" baseAuthorityPageNumber="271" baseAuthorityYear="1982" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="emeiensis">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF82FFCAB011FF7BFB4110FA" box="[1109,1252,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">R. emeiensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB309D2FF82FFCAB0B1FF7AFA0610FA" author="Zhu, Z. Y." box="[1269,1443,158,184]" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" pagination="271 - 272" refId="ref2845" refString="Zhu, Z. Y. (1982) A new species of Tupistra of E'meishan. Acta Botanica Yunnanica 4 (3): 271 - 272." type="journal article" year="1982">Zhu 1982: 271</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB309D2FF82FFCAB4CCFF26FEC1109E" author="Tanaka, N." box="[136,356,194,220]" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" pagination="329 - 333" refId="ref2636" refString="Tanaka, N. (2003) New combinations in Rohdea (Convallariaceae). Novon 13: 329 - 333. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3393269" type="journal article" year="2003">Tanaka (2003: 332)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
possess annulus appendage enclosed stamens or stamens situated inner annulus appendages. The new species more similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF82FFCAB59CFF03FD241142" authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="Chen" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[472,641,230,256]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verruculosa">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF82FFCAB59CFF03FD241142" box="[472,641,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">R. verruculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the lobes abaxially with verruculose in these two species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF82FFCAB4CCFEEFFE881166" authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Q. W. LIN" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,301,266,292]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="medogensis">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF82FFCAB4CCFEEFFE881166" box="[136,301,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">R. medogensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF82FFCAB58FFEEFFDD61166" authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="Chen" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[459,627,266,293]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verruculosa">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF82FFCAB58FFEEFFE791166" box="[459,476,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B956A831FF82FFCAB5A9FEEEFDD61166" box="[493,627,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">verruculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the characters of the short spike and peduncle. 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF82FFCAB08EFEEFFAD51166" authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Q. W. LIN" authorityYear="2022" box="[1226,1392,266,292]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="medogensis">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF82FFCAB08EFEEFFAD51166" box="[1226,1392,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">R. medogensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with several sterile bracts apically and it also has 3 fertile bracts per flower and the outer bract exceeding the flowers. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF82FFCAB1D7FECBFEAE112E" authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Q. W. LIN" authorityYear="2022" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="medogensis">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF82FFCAB1D7FECBFEAE112E" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">R. medogensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the perianth globular; lobes deltoid-ovate, very short, apical portion subacute, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF82FFCAB0E6FEB7FAED112E" authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="Chen" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[1186,1352,338,364]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verruculosa">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF82FFCAB0E6FEB7FAED112E" box="[1186,1352,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">R. verruculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
perianth subcampanulate, lobes ovate, apex cuspidate. And the style in 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF82FFCAB71BFE93FBA111D2" authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Q. W. LIN" authorityYear="2022" box="[863,1028,374,400]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="medogensis">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF82FFCAB71BFE93FBA111D2" box="[863,1028,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">R. medogensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was very conspicuous, ovary askew and stigma was bend and not lobed, but in 
<taxonomicName id="4C220FA0FF82FFCAB62EFE7FFCB511F6" authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="Chen" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[618,784,410,436]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verruculosa">
<emphasis id="B956A831FF82FFCAB62EFE7FFCB511F6" box="[618,784,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">R. verruculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the style was very short and ovary globose, the stigma was straight and 3-lobed. The floral traits of the two species are compared in 
<tableCitation id="C6A04198FF82FFCAB7F2FE5AFBAF119A" box="[950,1034,446,472]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,224,520,544]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison of several floral characters in species of Rohdea medogensis and R. verruculosa" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF5D24ABFF82FFCAB4CCFDECFB7B1262" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" tableUuid="DF5D24ABFF82FFCAB4CCFDECFB7B1262">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
